The thing is the UP on Sunfire (at least now) is better than Cinderhulk. The only real advantage Cinderhulk has that Sunfire doesn't is the percent-based health bonus, and the Sunfire is only SLIGHTLY more expensive. If there was a tank meta, it was incredibly short-lived.

All of the jungle items have a lane-item analog:

{{item:3709}} {{item:3717}} {{item:3721}} {{item:3725}} = {{item:3068}} 
{{item:3710}} {{item:3718}} {{item:3722}} {{item:3726}} = {{item:3091}} (also counts as continuing the Feral Flare's legacy)
{{item:3708}} {{item:3716}} {{item:3720}} {{item:3724}} = {{item:3165}} 
{{item:3707}} {{item:3714}} {{item:3719}} {{item:3723}} = {{item:3134}}

The jungle item counterparts are inherently weaker due to a lack of one stat or another along with the unique passive. Morellonomicon doesn't have the mana regen or the grevious wounds, Cinderhulk's immolation is not as strong as Sunfire, and Wit's End has neither the magic resist nor the drain. Funny enough, the Warrior enchantment is a step up from the Brutalizer, but it's also one that builds into another item.
